subsection.text:
              Subsection (f) of
			 section 223 of the Internal Revenue Code of 1986 is amended by adding at the
			 end the following new paragraph:


              Title XXVII of the
			 Public Health Service Act (
                42 U.S.C. 300gg et seq.
              ) is amended by adding at the
			 end the following new part:

clause.text:
the offer, sale,
				rating (including medical underwriting), renewal, and issuance of individual or
				group health insurance coverage to an individual;

the provision to
				an individual in relation to individual or group health insurance coverage of
				health care and insurance related services;

subparagraph.text:
to register with
				and designate the State insurance commissioner as its agent solely for the
				purpose of receiving service of legal documents or process;

to comply with the
				applicable requirements for independent review under section 2798 with respect
				to coverage offered in the State;

from terminating
				or discontinuing coverage or a class of coverage in accordance with subsections
				(b) and (c) of section 2742;

from raising
				premium rates for all policy holders within a class based on claims
				experience;

clause.text:
are based on
				specific wellness activities that are not applicable to all individuals;
				and

subparagraph.text:
each independent
				medical reviewer meets the qualifications described in paragraphs (2) and
				(3);

is appropriately
				credentialed or licensed in 1 or more States to deliver health care services;
				and

clause.text:
not have a
				material familial, financial, or professional relationship with such a party;
				and

subclause.text:
the affiliated
				individual is not involved in the provision of items or services in the case
				under review;

the affiliated
				individual is not an employee of the issuer and does not provide services
				exclusively or primarily to or on behalf of the issuer;

subparagraph.text:
the availability
			 and cost of health insurance policies for individuals with pre-existing medical
			 conditions;

clause.text:
making quarterly
				payments to the States under grants under this title in accordance with section
				2202(a);

approving
				entities under subsection (a)(3)(B) for purposes of the audits required under
				subsection (a);

paragraph.text:
disability under

                        section 504 of the Rehabilitation Act of 1973 (
                          29 U.S.C. 794
                        );

subparagraph.text:
health-care-related
				items and services that such State would provide payment for under this title,
				if provided to an indigent individual;
